                     "name":  "Daily News Review",
                     "prompt":  "0. **COMEX silver preflight** (run first, every time — this runs before the news check so a hard alert can lead the digest):\n   - Execute exactly: `python C:/Data/Hermes/skills/commodity-inventory-monitor/scripts/fetch_comex_inventory.py --metal silver --threshold 0.25 --state-file C:/Data/Hermes/cache/comex_inventory_history.jsonl`\n   - Parse the JSON line on stdout. Capture these fields for later: `registered_oz`, `eligible_oz`, `total_oz`, `registered_ratio`, `site_reported_ratio`, `alert`, `fetch_ok`.\n   - If `fetch_ok` is false (data source unreachable / parse error), treat silver as \"data unavailable\" and continue — the news digest MUST still ship. Never block the digest on the silver check.\n   - If `alert` is true, the registered-vs-total ratio has dropped below Bill\u0027s 0.25 (25%) trigger. The squeeze precursor is active.\n\n1. **Find today\u0027s news video**: Find the most recent video from the **Shared Sapience** YouTube channel. Use the query: `Shared Sapience TCR`. Select the latest video uploaded in the last 24-48 hours whose title contains \"TCR\" or a date reference. Note the video ID.\n\n2. **Validate the video**: Before analyzing, verify:\n   - The video is NOT a music video, reaction video, or entertainment content\n   - The video was uploaded within the last 48 hours\n   - The video with the same ID has not been analyzed yet.\n\n3. If no new or valid news video is found, emit \"Repeat:\" + previous video analysis, which includes the video title, for the latest video, and end the job. (Still include the Market Pulse — see step 5.)\n\n4. If the video is new, follow the loaded `daily-news-digest` skill. It orchestrates the full pipeline and delegates the analysis step and format spec to `youtube-news-digest`. The format skill is the source of truth for the digest structure — do not re-derive it here.\n\n5. **Compose the final message**:\n   - Run the daily-news-digest skill to produce the news digest body.\n   - **ALERT prefix (conditional)**: If `alert` is true, prepend the following block ABOVE the news digest:\n     ```\n     🚨 COMEX SILVER ALERT — registered ratio at {registered_ratio*100:.1f}% (below your 0.25 trigger).\n     Registered: {registered_oz/1e6:.0f}M oz | Eligible: {eligible_oz/1e6:.0f}M oz | Total: {total_oz/1e6:.0f}M oz\n     Registered stock thin enough to signal squeeze dynamics. See today\u0027s digest for context.\n     ```\n   - **Market Pulse (always, when fetch_ok)**: Append the following block to the END of the message (before the source link/URL the format skill adds):\n     ```\n     ---\n     📊 Market Pulse — COMEX Silver\n     Registered: {registered_oz/1e6:.0f}M oz ({registered_ratio*100:.1f}% of total)\n     Eligible:   {eligible_oz/1e6:.0f}M oz\n     Total:      {total_oz/1e6:.0f}M oz\n     Source: silverdata.io\n     Status: {ALERT — below 0.25 threshold | normal}\n     ```\n   - If `fetch_ok` is false, omit the Market Pulse block entirely (don\u0027t ship partial data).\n   - Write the assembled message body to /tmp/digest.txt.\n\n6. **Deliver the digest** to the configured target. This job\u0027s `deliver` field is set (currently `telegram`), so:\n   - Run `hermes send --list` to confirm the platform is configured.\n   - If configured, run `hermes send --to \u003ctarget\u003e --file /tmp/digest.txt` to route the digest.\n   - If the platform is not configured, surface that honestly and still emit the digest in the chat response so nothing is lost.\n   - The format skill (`youtube-news-digest`) handles the actual `hermes send` invocation and the platform check when a `deliver_to` parameter is passed in.\n\nIf any step fails, emit: \"Daily News job failed at step [N]: [error]. Manual review needed.\"\n",
